      • loadClass

        protected Class<?> loadClass(String name)
                      throws ClassNotFoundException
        Loads a Class named by the supplied name and returns it.

        This method may return null.

        This implementation first checks to see if the supplied name is null. If it is, then null is returned. Otherwise, the Class.forName(String, boolean, ClassLoader) method is called with the supplied name, true and the result of calling the Thread.getContextClassLoader() method on the current Thread as arguments, and its result is returned.

        Parameters:
        name - the name of the Class to load; may be null in which case null will be returned
        Returns:
        a Class corresponding to the supplied name, or null
        Throws:
        ClassNotFoundException - if the Class.forName(String, boolean, ClassLoader) method threw a ClassNotFoundException
        See Also:
        Class.forName(String, boolean, ClassLoader), Thread.getContextClassLoader()
